review_blob: One of the first stouts I've tried. Taste was like burnt coffee, but not in a bad way necessarily. Pours quite thick with a nice head. Not sure if I'd seek out this beer again, but I'll definitely finish up the 6-pack.
I really enjoyed this beer, moreso than the lindemans kreik. Nice raspberry aroma, looks quite attractive when poured out. Definitely very sweet, but highly enjoyable.
This was my first lambic, I really enjoyed it. It was a little sweet, but I like that. The aroma was a bit like cough syrup, but the taste was smooth. I definitely enjoyed it.
